\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces The three objective families' intrinsic reward over training, all with soil-only conditioning, all on the same simulator. Top: distance-maximizing --- reward \emph  {grows} as digging improves (it telescopes; only net transport pays). Middle: MI --- \emph  {saturates} within a few thousand steps and flatlines. Bottom: dynamics-predictability --- \emph  {starves} to exactly zero. This single figure is the taxonomy.}}{21}{figure.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:mechanisms}{{7}{21}{The three objective families' intrinsic reward over training, all with soil-only conditioning, all on the same simulator. Top: distance-maximizing --- reward \emph {grows} as digging improves (it telescopes; only net transport pays). Middle: MI --- \emph {saturates} within a few thousand steps and flatlines. Bottom: dynamics-predictability --- \emph {starves} to exactly zero. This single figure is the taxonomy}{figure.7}{}}
